data.param: {"callBackUrl":"https://api.example.com/callback","customMode":false,"instrumental":false,"model":"V5","prompt":"A heartbreaking Country ballad about A wet pair of socks. Short song, approx 30 seconds."}

sunoData.prompt:
[Verse]
Rain poured down, the sky turned gray,
Boots gave out halfway through the day.
Each step squished, cold seeped in,
A soggy fight I couldn’t win.

[Chorus]
Oh, these wet socks, they drag me down,
Heavy as heartache in this old town.
Each drip reminds me, I’ve lost control,
Soaked to the skin, and soaked to the soul.

[Outro]
They say dry feet can save a man,
But here I stand, a sinking sand.
sunoData.title: Soaked to the Soul
sunoData.tags: ballad, slow ballad, plaintive male vocals, acoustic with soft fingerpicking, country
